data.enText: to put furniture in a house, room, etc.
The room was furnished with antiques.

data.chText: 向（某人 / 某事物）供应，提供
data.enText: to supply or provide sb/sth with sth; to supply sth to sb

data.chText: 她向他提供了与案件有关的事实。
data.enText: She furnished him with the facts surrounding the case.

means: 向(某人 / 某事物)供应，提供

ex.chText: 他的房间只摆放了一张书桌、一把椅子和一张床。
ex.enText: His room is only furnished with a desk, a chair and a bed.

ex.chText: 尽管他们自己买的房子，他们仍然有钱配备家具。
ex.enText: They still can afford to furnish it despite the fact that they bought the house themselves.

synonyms.bx: 指用家具布置房屋或房间。

ex.chText: 这个车间安装了一条装配线。
ex.enText: The workshop is equipped with an assembly line.

ex.chText: 他们给所有屋子安装摄像机花了很多钱。
ex.enText: They have spent a lot of money equipping all the rooms with video cameras.

synonyms.bx: 指向某人或某地提供必要的设备以进行某项活动或工作。

ex.chText: 这艘军舰配备了新雷达。
ex.enText: The warship was fitted out with a new radar.

ex.chText: 士兵们配发了武器。
ex.enText: The soldiers were fitted out with weapons.

synonyms.bx: 指向某人或某地提供必要的设备、家具或衣服。

ex.chText: 经理拿了一支烟给他。
ex.enText: The manager offered him a cigarette.

ex.chText: 他给我提供了避难处。
ex.enText: He offered me shelter.

ex.chText: 他给她提供了一份好工作，但她拒绝了。
ex.enText: He offered her a good job, but she turned it down.

synonyms.bx: 指主动给予帮助等，对方可以接受也可以拒绝。

ex.chText: 这房间可以看到迷人的海景。
ex.enText: The room affords a fascinating sea view.

ex.chText: 这给了他与外国的同龄人交流的机会。
ex.enText: It afforded him the opportunity to communicate with his foreign peers.

synonyms.bx: 多指提供抽象的东西，可后接双宾语。

ex.chText: 这些新的发现是否会提供更多与案件有关的线索？
ex.enText: Will these new finds furnish more clues surrounding the case?

ex.chText: 他得到了一份当地经销商的名单。
ex.enText: He was furnished with a list of local dealers.

synonyms.bx: 既可指提供抽象的东西，又可指提供具体的东西。

ex.chText: 这家餐厅为客人提供免费甜点。
ex.enText: The restaurant provides free desserts for guests.

ex.chText: 他们已给我提供了所需要的一切。
ex.enText: They have already provided me with everything I need.

ex.chText: 孩子们有良好的衣食供应。
ex.enText: The kids are provided with good food and clothing.

ex.chText: 当局有义务为老年人提供住所。
ex.enText: It is the duty of the authorities to provide homes for the old.

synonyms.bx: 指为某人提供需要或有用的东西，多用于 provide sth for sb 和provide sb with sth 结构中。

ex.chText: 这个项目所用的钢材由一家国际公司提供。
ex.enText: Steel for this project was supplied by an international company.

ex.chText: 他们因为向街头小贩提供假药而被捕。
ex.enText: They were arrested for supplying counterfeit medicine to street vendors.

ex.chText: 母牛供给我们牛奶。
ex.enText: Cows supply us with milk.

ex.chText: 我们给附近的5个城镇提供电力。
ex.enText: We supply power to the five nearby towns.

synonyms.bx: 尤指长时间地定期供应所需或想要之物，多用于 supply sb with sth 和 supply sth to sb 结构中。

tr: give something useful or necessary to
example: We provided the room with an electrical heater
We furnished the house in the Biedermeyer style

value.def: If you furnish a room or building, you put furniture and furnishings into it.

example.ex: Many proprietors try to furnish their hotels with antiques.
example.tran: 许多经营者都想用古董装饰他们的酒店。

value.tran: 布置;为(房间或建筑物)配备家具陈设

value.def: If you furnish someone with something, you provide or supply it.

example.ex: They'll be able to furnish you with the rest of the details.
example.tran: 他们将可向你提供其余的细节。
